Pre-Game Insights: Denmark seek their first win in five matches as they return to Parken Stadion after their Euro 2024 exit.
Switzerland aim to build on their strong form, having won eight of their last nine games.
Denmark's interim coach Lars Knudsen will rely on experienced players like Kasper Schmeichel and Christian Eriksen.
Switzerland's key players include Granit Xhaka and Xherdan Shaqiri, who are both crucial to their team's success.
Both teams have suffered injuries, with Denmark missing Rasmus Hojlund and Switzerland losing Yann Sommer and Xherdan Shaqiri.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match is part of the UEFA Nations League Group A4, which also includes Spain, Portugal, and the Czech Republic.
Denmark and Switzerland have both reached the knockout phase of Euro 2024, adding context to their Nations League campaign.
Others: The match is expected to be a challenging one for both teams, with Denmark's home advantage and Switzerland's strong recent form.
